Babu Frik Help Menu
Syntax: ~bank set <to> <creds>
Set the balance of a user's bank account.
Putting + or - signs before the amount will add/remove currency on the user's bank account instead. Examples:
  • ~bank set @Twentysix 26 - Sets balance to 26
  • ~bank set @Twentysix +2 - Increases balance by 2
  • ~bank set @Twentysix -6 - Decreases balance by 6
Arguments
  • <to> The user to set the currency of.
  • <creds> The amount of currency to set their balance to.
Type ~help <command> for more info on a command. You can also type ~help <category> for more info on a category.
